			<h3 ><a href="#p2026">Re: Artemis Aspect for C#?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=2026&amp;sid=665fec9c4b1a7904836d782e90d8f066#p2026"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2&amp;sid=665fec9c4b1a7904836d782e90d8f066" style="color: #AA0000;" class="username-coloured">ploobsadmin</a></strong> &raquo; 22 Jan 2013, 21:46 </p>

			

			<div class="content">You can also Customize by yourself the way EntitySystem evaluate what Entity will be processed<br />Just override the method public virtual void OnChange(Entity e)<br /><br />For now it only use bit operations to discover if an entity has the required types and if it has already been added this EntitySystem.<br /><br />Take a look here: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://github.com/thelinuxlich/artemis_CSharp/blob/master/Artemis_XNA_INDEPENDENT/EntitySystem.cs">https://github.com/thelinuxlich/artemis ... ySystem.cs</a><!-- m --></div>

			

		</div>

		
