			<h3 ><a href="#p2031">Re: Artemis Aspect for C#?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=2031&amp;sid=665fec9c4b1a7904836d782e90d8f066#p2031"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=303&amp;sid=665fec9c4b1a7904836d782e90d8f066">Seismo</a></strong> &raquo; 20 Fev 2013, 09:59 </p>

			

			<div class="content">Gentlemen, i have fiddled around a bit with your approach and found some issues you may want to fix in your release. First of all you should use SortedDictionary for EntitySystems actives (private Dictionary&lt;int,Entity&gt; actives... -&gt; private readonly SortedDictionary&lt;int,Entity&gt; actives...), otherwise you will have strange results on chained entities (The order of items in standard Dictionary is random!). You also should make this dictionary readonly or volatile if you plan to support multitasking features. Same for drawLayers and updateLayers in SystemManger. Then i miss a simple way to delete all entities at once, a Clear() sub, maybe in EntityWorld would be nice, i need this feature if i want to load a new level. Please do not hesitate to ask me if anything is not clear. Keep up the good work.</div>

			

		</div>

		
