			<h3 ><a href="#p2035">Re: Artemis Aspect for C#?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=2035&amp;sid=665fec9c4b1a7904836d782e90d8f066#p2035"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54&amp;sid=665fec9c4b1a7904836d782e90d8f066" style="color: #000066;" class="username-coloured">tpastor</a></strong> &raquo; 22 Fev 2013, 11:26 </p>

			

			<div class="content">why we need to make it volatile or readonly.<br />The multithread aproaches works dividing in two ways<br />- or for each system, we create multiple threads and process its entities  in paralell  (systems as processed serially, entities in a system are paralleled)<br />-or we proccess all systems of a specific layer in parallel (all entities of a system is processed serially, the systems are paralled)<br /><br />why these dictionaries needs to be volatile ? (add or remove entities are delayed until next frame, they are processed serially also ...)<br /><br /><br />The clear method is a good sugestion, i will consider adding it !!!</div>

